        //
        // The example for n=5: [13, 4, 20, 13, 2, 5, 8, 3, 17, 16]. Sorted: [2, 3, 4, 5, 8, 13, 13, 16, 17, 20]. n=5 is odd.
        // $a_0=2, a_1=3, a_2=4, a_3=5, a_4=8, a_5=13, a_6=13, a_7=16, a_8=17, a_9=20$.
        // Using the formula $a_n - a_{n-1}$: $a_5 - a_4 = 13 - 8 = 5$. This matches.
        //
        // It seems the answer is always $a_n - a_{n-1}$ (using 0-indexed array $a_0, \dots, a_{2n-1}$).
