        // where k ranges from (2n - 1) down to (n).
        // This ensures:
        // 1. All numbers are even, so gcd(a, b) >= 2.
        // 2. For any two chosen numbers 2*k1 and 2*k2,
        //    k1 and k2 are distinct integers in the range [n, 2n-1].
        //    Since k1, k2 are distinct and in this range,
        //    neither k1 divides k2 nor k2 divides k1 (unless k1=k2, which is not allowed).
        //    Specifically, if k1 < k2, then k2/k1 > 1.
        //    Since k1 >= n, k2 <= 2n-1, k2/k1 < (2n-1)/n < 2 for n > 1.
